	)
	(text "Disk activity is monitored via the Pico's \ninternal pull-up resistor on the GPIO, \nwith a BAT43 Schottky diode providing level \nisolation to protect the 3.3V logic from the \n5V IDE bus while maintaining a valid \nlogic-low threshold\n\nWhen the IDE controller pulls Pin 39 to \nground (Active low) the diode conducts \nand brings the GPIO low; conversely, \nwhen the bus is idle or at 5V, the diode \nblocks current flow,allowing the internal \npull-up to safely maintain a 3.3V \nlogic-high state"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 238.252 127.508 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "0570e9b3-970a-4a11-963b-d60a8f5e030d")
	)
